[The hantavirus in this month's [August 2012] reports from California is doubtless Sin Nombre virus, which is endemic there. Its rodent host is the deer mouse, _Peromyscus maniculatus_. It is unusual to have these 6 cases occur in a single, very limited focal area, Curry Village, within the space of 2 months. This suggests that the deer mouse population is abundant in Curry Village, and perhaps supporting active virus transmission and shedding there at this time.

An image of _Peromyscus maniculatus_, the rodent host of Sin Nombre virus, can be accessed at http://www.ask.com/wiki/Peromyscus_maniculatus.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Yosemite National Park can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/3bLD. - Mod.TY]
